Package prkmodel.utils

Interface NervousSystemElementFactory

Type Parameters:
T - the type of object that this factory creates
All Known Implementing Classes:
RepastNervousSystemElementFactory
public interface NervousSystemElementFactory
Interface representing a factory for creating elements of the nervous system. It provides methods to create and configure NervousSystemElement instances.

This interface follows the Factory design pattern, which promotes the creation of objects without specifying the exact class of object that will be created.

    • create

      NervousSystemElement create(ModelElementType type, double x, double y, double z)
      Creates a new NervousSystemElement of the specified type at the given coordinates.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of the element to create.
      x - the X coordinate for the element.
      y - the Y coordinate for the element.
      z - the Z coordinate for the element.
      Returns:
      the created NervousSystemElement.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the type is null.
      IllegalArgumentException - if the coordinates are invalid.
